{
  "text": "Quantification of the target VOCs was performed using the internal standard curves method with four internal standards (bromochloromethane, 1,4-difluorobenzene, chlorobenzene-d5 and 3-bromofluorobenzene), and the corresponding VOCs of each internal standard see [CITATION_1] . The correlation coefficients of the curves ranged from 0.900 to 1.000. In this study, 63 VOCs were measured in atmospheric samples from Mount Tai in July 2015, including alkanes, alkenes, aromatics, halocarbons and OVOCs, as shown in Table 1 .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "55781808"
